## 6. Response Procedures

### 6.1 Critical Risk — Immediate Block

1. **Block access** to the AI service within 4 hours of discovery via DNS/proxy/firewall
2. **Notify** {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "the AI governance contact" }} immediately
3. **Assess data exposure** — determine what data was processed, volume, and duration
4. **Evaluate NDB obligation** — assess whether a Notifiable Data Breach has occurred under Part IIIC of the Privacy Act
{% if ndb_ai_process %}5. **Follow the AI-specific NDB process** already established at {{ business_name }}{% else %}5. **Consult legal counsel** to determine NDB reporting obligations to the OAIC{% endif %}
6. **Preserve evidence** — retain logs, screenshots, and access records
7. **Conduct affected individual assessment** — determine if individuals must be notified
8. **Document** the incident in the AI Incident Register
{% if ai_incident_register %}9. **Update** {{ business_name }}'s AI Incident Register with full details{% else %}9. **Establish** an AI Incident Register if one does not yet exist{% endif %}

### 6.2 High Risk — Block and Assess

1. **Block access** within 24 hours of discovery
2. **Notify** {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "the AI governance contact" }} within 24 hours
3. **Interview the user(s)** to understand the use case, data processed, and duration
4. **Determine** if the tool can be rapidly evaluated through the AI Procurement Policy
5. **If approvable**, place in Tolerated status (maximum 30 days) while evaluation is completed
6. **If not approvable**, confirm block and communicate to affected users
7. **Document** in the AI Incident Register

### 6.3 Medium Risk — Assess and Decide

1. **Notify** {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "the AI governance contact" }} within 5 business days
2. **Place in Tolerated status** (maximum 60 days) while evaluation proceeds
3. **Require the user** to submit an AI Procurement Request within 10 business days
4. **Monitor usage** during the assessment period
5. **Approve or block** based on the evaluation outcome

### 6.4 Low Risk — Monitor and Formalise

1. **Log the discovery** in the Shadow AI Discovery Register
2. **Request the user** to submit an AI Procurement Request within 30 days
3. **If the tool passes evaluation**, add to the Sanctioned AI register
4. **If the user does not submit a request**, escalate to their line manager

